HEADWORD: Inexsuperable
<hw>In`ex*su"per*a*ble</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>inexsuperabilis</ets>; pref. <ets>in-</ets> not +
<ets>exsuperabilis</ets> that may be surmounted. See <er>In-</er> not,
<er>Ex-</er>, and <er>Superable</er>.]</ety> <def>Not capable of being
passed over; insuperable; insurmountable.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

